From: cj-vana <cj@depth23.online>
Date: Sat, 16 May 2026 20:31:12 -0600
Subject: [PATCH 10/15] Widen coordinator delays a tiny bit more

~25% bump across the main coordination knobs:
- BOT_RESPONSE_DELAY_BASE_MILLIS   1200 -> 1500
- BOT_RESPONSE_DELAY_JITTER_MILLIS 1800 -> 2200
- BOT_HOP_STEP_MILLIS_DEFAULT      2500 -> 3000
- BOT_HOP_BIAS_MAX_MILLIS         12000 -> 15000
- BOT_RESPONSE_PENDING_TTL_MILLIS 60000 -> 75000

BOT_PREFS_VERSION bumped 4 -> 5 so existing bots re-derive the new
hop_step_ms default instead of carrying the old value.

Gives near and far bots more breathing room so far bots reliably hear
near bots' acks before firing their own (token suppression). Worst-case
6-hop scheduled delay rises from ~17.6s to ~22.5s, still well under the
new 75s TTL.
---
 examples/companion_radio/BotTypes.h | 12 ++++++------
 1 file changed, 6 insertions(+), 6 deletions(-)

